Pre-Game Insights: Interim England boss Lee Carsley makes his Wembley bow as his side hosts Finland in Nations League Group B2.
Lee Carsley is stepping up from his role with the England U21s to become Gareth Southgate's temporary successor.
England are in a new era with Lee Carsley at the helm, aiming to impress in the Nations League.
Finland, under coach Markku Kanerva since 2016, aims to qualify for the 2026 World Cup.
Key players to watch include Teemu Pukki, Glen Kamara, and Viljami Sinisalo.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be shown live on ITV1 with live coverage starting from 6:45pm.
Fans can stream the match online via ITVX.
Radio coverage is available on BBC Radio 5 Live and talkSPORT.
Others: Odds for the match: England (1/7), Draw (15/2), Finland (14/1).
